<subSubSection id="AFEB6501FFB37358D49AF884FDEFFF4C" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="398" pageId="11" pageNumber="397" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="E74E368AFFB37358D49AF884FDEFFF4C" blockId="11.[151,1437,900,2014]" lastBlockId="12.[151,1436,151,213]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="398" pageId="11" pageNumber="397">
<emphasis id="D585EA98FFB3735FD49AF884FEFCF80B" bold="true" box="[199,315,1913,1938]" pageId="11" pageNumber="397">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="20F14D09FFB3735FD51FF887FDA6F80B" box="[322,609,1913,1938]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Bactrocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipunctata">
<emphasis id="D585EA98FFB3735FD51FF887FDA6F80B" box="[322,609,1913,1938]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="397">Bactrocera brevipunctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="20F14D09FFB3735FD773F887FC54F80B" authority="" authorityName="" box="[814,915,1913,1938]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Sinodacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hochii">
<emphasis id="D585EA98FFB3735FD773F887FC54F80B" box="[814,915,1913,1938]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="397">B. hochii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in general scutal, abdominal and wing pattern but can be differentiated by the reduced presutural spots, larger fuscous apical spot on the wing (reaching apices of vein R2+3 and dm-cu crossvein basally) and extensive fuscous areas of all femora. It keys to couplet 
<quantity id="20099B6FFFB3735FD15CF83CFAEBF843" box="[1281,1324,1985,2010]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.524" pageId="11" pageNumber="397" unit="in" value="6.0">6 in</quantity>
subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="20F14D09FFB47358D4CAFF6AFECDFF29" authority="" authorityName="" box="[151,266,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Sinodacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D585EA98FFB47358D4CAFF6AFECDFF29" box="[151,266,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="398">Sinodacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the key of 
<bibRefCitation id="83604B7BFFB47358D5F4FF65FD06FF29" author="Drew" box="[425,705,151,176]" pageId="12" pageNumber="398" refString="Drew, R. A. I. &amp; Romig, M. C. (2016) Keys to the tropical fruit flies (Tephritidae: Dacinae) of South-East Asia. CAB International, Wallingford, 487 pp." type="book" year="2016">Drew and Romig (2016)</bibRefCitation>
, differing from both 
<taxonomicName id="20F14D09FFB47358D7F3FF64FB66FF29" authority="Enderlein" authorityName="Enderlein" box="[942,1185,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Bactrocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infesta">
<emphasis id="D585EA98FFB47358D7F3FF64FBDEFF29" box="[942,1049,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="398">B. infesta</emphasis>
(Enderlein)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="20F14D09FFB47358D085FF64FAB9FF29" authority="Zia" authorityName="Zia" authorityYear="1936" box="[1240,1406,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Sinodacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hochii">
<emphasis id="D585EA98FFB47358D085FF64FAF9FF29" box="[1240,1342,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="398">B. hochii</emphasis>
(Zia)
</taxonomicName>
in the broader apical spot on the wing.
</paragraph>
